    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is the CT Aortogram painful? ",
        "answer": " No. You may feel a warm flush or metallic taste for a few seconds—that’s normal.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How long does the entire visit take?",
        "answer": " 60 minutes: 15 min preparation, 10 min scan, 30 min observation.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": " Can I drive home after the scan? ",
        "answer": " Yes, unless you’ve taken a sedative for claustrophobia.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Is radiation harmful? ",
        "answer": " We follow ALARA (As Low As Reasonably Achievable) principles; the dose is well within safe limits for diagnostic benefit.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Will I need the scan yearly? ",
        "answer": " Only if you have an enlarging aneurysm or graft; otherwise every 2–5 years is typical.\n"
      }
    ],
